subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum moderately convex, 2.4 times as wide as long, posterior angles obtuse-angled; lateroposterior depressions small, shallow, situated at posterior corners of pronotum; 
"agriloid"
carina sharp, reaching midlength of lateral margins, very close to the lateral pronotal carina; pronotal sculpture consisting of very fine, almost indistinct, transversely widened cells and rugae; basal tubercles missing, prescutellar pit wide but shallow. Scutellum small, triangular, weakly depressed, microsculptured, slightly longer than wide.

Aedeagus (Figs 76, 77 in 
Cobos 1956
) short, widely spindle-shaped, median lobe pointed apically.
